The paper discusses reinforcement learning in the context of Markov decision processes (MDPs) with a focus on risk-constrained policies. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and multiagent systems (cs.MA). The use of UCT-like search and a predictor learned through interaction with the MDP (in the style of AlphaZero) also suggests a focus on algorithmic and computational aspects, which further supports the relevance of these sub-categories.
